{"word":"διανοέομαι","slug":"διανοέομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>διανοέομαι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-νοήσομαι</el>) (aor1 <el>διενοήθην</el>) (<a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>διανενόημαι</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νοέω'><el>νοέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a>: <i>to be minded, intend, purpose</i> to do, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to think over</i> or <i>of</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>meditari</el>, <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to think</i> or <i>suppose</i> that, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b>with <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>to be minded</i> or <i>disposed</i> so and so, <el>καλῶς, κακῶς δ.</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}